Eurocement plant receives visit from President | World Cement Mordovcement modernisation project progressing well Mordovcement modernisation project progressing well Save to read list Published by Katherine Guenioui , Editor World Cement , Tuesday, 24 March 2015 08:45 Advertisement Mordovcement Mordovcement is the latest plant to have received a visit from Eurocement President Mikhail Skorokhod, who joined other senior staff members to tour the plant and discuss key issues for the plant this year. 
Particular attention was paid to health and safety and product quality. 
The plant is currently undergoing a modernisation project. 
The project is in its final stage and completion is scheduled for 15 April. 
Oskolcement Another Eurocement plant, Oskolcement, has launched a new brand of cement: CEM II / A-SH 42.5 N. This brings its product range to six types of cement. 
Portland cement CEM II / A-SH 42.5 N is a slag cement ideal for use in precast concrete elements and for small-sized products. 
The concrete produced with this type of cement has a high initial and final strength. 
It has a high resistance to frost, which makes it suited to freeze-thaw conditions. 
Adapted from press release by Katherine Guenioui Read the article online at: https://www.worldcement.com/europe-cis/24032015/mordovcement-modernisation-project-progressing-well-565/ You might also like   Construction materials company, Summit Materials, Inc.
, has announced results for the fourth quarter and full year 2019.   
Monday, 23 March 2015 09:30 The Eurocement plant beat its planned production for the month and increased its production year-on-year. 
Eurocement President Mikhail Skorokhod visited the new plant with the Governor of the Ulyanovsk region, Sergey Morozov. 
Thursday, 12 March 2015 10:00 The Eurocement-owned company produced 187 000 t of clinker in the first two months of this year, up 3% y/y. 
